</p><h2 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-10_">The role of the thyroid gland in your body
</h2><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-12_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3" data-animation="fadeIn">The thyroid is a small gland that sits in your windpipe and covers it from three sides. It is responsible for breaking proteins and processing vitamins and carbs. Hormones of the thyroid help regulate metabolism and manage other vital hormones of the body (such as dopamine, and adrenaline). 
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-14_">What is hypothyroidism?
</h3><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-16_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3" data-animation="fadeIn">Hypothyroidism — or underactive thyroid — occurs when the body is unable to produce enough thyroid hormones. The symptoms of hypothyroidism&nbsp;include:
